{"name":"Branded a Coward","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":1,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Whether true or not, this character has been branded a coward. In Dwarven society, this stain comes not from breaking an oath, but from refusing to swear the oath in the first place. Branded a Coward grants the character a 1D infamous reputation with either Dwarven Nobles, Clansmen, Guilders, Artificers or the Host. Player's choice. And more important, this Dwarf may not swear an Oath until he has redeemed himself in the eyes of his longbeard.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":true,"reputationName":"Either Dwarven Nobles, Clansmen, Guilders, Artificers or the Host. Player's choice","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TtqjBPpwU1Bk1I1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0SToFHnklYSBEI5I"}
{"name":"Oathswearer","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Long has it been the tradition of the great Dwarven Princes to go before the Longbeards of the clans to receive their blessing and swear an oath to protect them and uphold the traditions of their forefathers . Oathswearer is perhaps the most vital trait in Dwarven culture. Though all Dwarves are Oathsworn, only those with the Oathswearer trait may pronounce a binding pact. Any oath taken while not under the guidance of an Oathswearer is not binding. Any oath pronounced before an Oathswearer must be written into the character's Beliefs. It usually replaces one of the character's existing three Beliefs. It can be used to replace the fourth,\nOathsworn trait belief only if that oath has been satisfied. If an Oathswearer demands a character's word, and the character refuses, the Oathswearer can, at his\ndiscretion, brand him a coward. It is a stain that all Dwarves recognize, and no oaths or agreements are made with cowards. The character is given the Branded a Coward trait.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"3Vrcb3XlbR77Zj4u"}
{"name":"Oddly Likeable","type":"trait","img":"icons/commodities/tech/cog-gold.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"character","text":"No matter how outrageous his deeds or words, there's just something about this Dwarf that's charming and likeable.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"","reputationDice":0,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TtqjBPpwU1Bk1I1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"BPAOj7xYcYtW8ypx"}
{"name":"Stone-Faced","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"This trait cancels the effects of the Discerner song and any other trait or special ability that allows the character to be \"read.\" However, it doesn't count against Aura Reading with the Magesense or Second Sight. It also adds +2D to Falsehood and Gambling.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KUIWCvz2hUZ7t9UA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DlESALEM42HfmQPk"}
{"name":"Galvanizing Presence","type":"trait","img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-blue.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"call-on","text":"Galvanizing Presence is a call-on for Command or Conspicuous. Pick one.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"","reputationDice":0,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"Command or Conspicuous. Pick one.","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QR0fN9Psb0r7PbdA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"F2RUkcuU4mt8zqz6"}
{"name":"Accustomed to the Dark","type":"trait","img":"icons/commodities/tech/cog-gold.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Contrary to popular belief, Dwarves cannot see in darkness. However, because they have lived many ages in halls lit by firelight and reflected sunlight, Dwarves do not suffer any penalty for twilight, starlight, candlelight, lamplight or torchlight. They do suffer from complete darkness as Men and Elves do. \n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"GnjPq1cet1yXEc06"}
{"name":"Shaped from Earth and Stone","type":"trait","img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-blue.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"In the first age, when the earth was barren, Dwarves were created by the One Who Most Dearly Loves to Shape with His Hands. Dwarves were born beneath the earth and it was long before they came forth into the light of the sun. In these dark ages, they grew familiar with the ores, veins, rocks and sediments that were their sky, ocean and earth. Attendant with their appreciation of raw materials is a love of building and shaping. Due to their heritage, above all else it is craftsmanship and the beauty of that which is wrought by skill that Dwarves love most. And since they were Born Under Earth, metals, stones and gems are their first love-far beyond cloth, wood or leather. This trait also gives the Dwarves access to natural magic abilities-open-ended/special skills for most of their crafts and arts.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KUIWCvz2hUZ7t9UA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"I4LsMZXMVkimdC5l"}
{"name":"Affinity for Sheep and Goats","type":"trait","img":"icons/commodities/tech/cog-gold.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"This trait adds +1D to any skill or stat when dealing with sheep or goats.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":true,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"Any skill or stat when dealing with sheep or goats.","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All Circles tests when dealing with Artificers or Noble Born Dwarves","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"Minor affiliation (1D) outside the Dwarf hold","affiliationDice":1,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JD1VvfGxq3GQSJsP"}
{"name":"Dvergar","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Dvergar are original, mythical Dwarves. Dwarven nobility all lay claim of blood ties to these ancient forebears. This trait grants a 1D affiliation with other Dwarven nobility and a 1D reputation among all Dwarves as a noble. Characters with this trait suffer a +1 Ob to all Inconspicuous tests among Dwarves.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":true,"obModifierTarget":"All Inconspicuous tests among Dwarves","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":true,"reputationName":"Dwarves as a whole","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":true,"affiliationName":"Other Dwarven nobility","affiliationDice":1,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KeMtHO2tXYICSSkG"}
{"name":"Tinkerer","type":"trait","img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-blue.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"call-on","text":"This trait acts as a call-on for Mending or Black-Metal Artifice when trying to cobble together something new or weird.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"","reputationDice":0,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"Mending or Black-Metal Artifice when trying to cobble together something new or weird.","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TtqjBPpwU1Bk1I1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LuBJscGvAXGJO6lv"}
{"name":"Quick-Step","type":"trait","img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-blue.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"call-on","text":"Wordbearers must hustle from the Miller to the Brewer, from the Quartermaster to the Khirurgeon, and from the Trader to the Longbeard. This trait acts as a call-on for any Speed test where the Dwarf is hurrying or hustling\n(including running to escape or maneuvering for a positioning test).\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"","reputationDice":0,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"Any Speed test where the Dwarf is hurrying or hustling","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zML3IIii96Gmf3Jt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NFPbGCcXVdaGM3tS"}
{"name":"Grudgekeeper","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":1,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"This character contains within him the capacity to maintain terrible enmity for perceived slights. He swears grudges like others swear oaths. The Grudgekeeper trait allows the player to replace his Oathsworn Belief with a Grudge. Rather than a promise or an oath, he swears revenge. Grudges follow the same mechanic as oaths. If the character has the Oathswearer trait, it combines with Grudgekeeper. He may only pronounce grudges rather than oaths-between two characters. They must write them into their Beliefs as if they were oaths.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarves only, special trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarves only, special trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"RW5zs9orDleHKw6M"}
{"name":"Hard as Nails","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"The Warden may choose to ignore one wound once per conflict. He may do as long as the wounded dice penalty is not greater than his current Will. So if he's only got 1D of Will left, he can't ignore a traumatic wound, but he can ignore a light.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VAi4pT5TXPcBzfMS"}
{"name":"Adventurer","type":"trait","img":"icons/commodities/tech/cog-gold.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Dwarven society is very structured and rigid. Those that break its conventions are forever branded as outsiders-even if they're later let back into the fold. Characters who were once Adventurers bear the stain of their deeds for the rest of their lives. No matter how hard they try to hide it, other Dwarves can just smell\nit on them. Adventurers gain +1 Ob to all Circles tests when dealing with Artificers or Noble Born Dwarves. However, Adventurers may choose a minor affiliation (1D) outside the Dwarf hold for free.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":true,"obModifierTarget":"All Circles tests when dealing with Artificers or Noble Born Dwarves","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":true,"affiliationName":"Minor affiliation (1D) outside the Dwarf hold","affiliationDice":1,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Wzm4YzLOKILCPJQq"}
{"name":"Oathsworn","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"All Dwarves have stern values hammered into their skulls from a very early age. In fact, Dwarven society is a complex and interlocking network of promises and traditions. The most prime among them is: \"Honor the oath.\" To break an oath is to break tradition that has seen Dwarves through many dark ages. It is a terrible crime and one not easily forgiven or forgotten.\n\nDue to this trait, all Dwarf characters start the game with an additional (fourth) Belief. This Belief must come in the form of an oath, and represents a pre-game bond between the Dwarf and one of his relationships. Oaths that pertain to the situation in play fill one of the standard three Belief slots. Acceptable oaths are: the soldier's oath: \"I owe Burri a debt of honor;\" the uncle's: \"I swore to recover the crown for my brother;\" the prince's vow: \"My father's last words were to rule wisely; this I swore\" and the drunk promises his wife: \"I vow never to go near the beer again.\" Yes, the requirements of an oath mean a Dwarf character must start with a relationship.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"XiLR5DDD8oX3wRl1"}
{"name":"Oathbreaker","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"A character who breaks an oath, lies while under oath or fails to fulfill an oath is forever marked as an Oathbreaker. While Oathbreakers are tolerated in Dwarven society, they are also mistrusted. No oaths may be sworn with an Oathbreaker until he has somehow resolved his initial betrayal. Also, the player must choose a relationship at the start of play that encompasses his broken oath . Lastly, Oathbreaker grants a 1D infamous reputation among the Nobles, Host, Artificers, Guilders or Clans. Player's choice.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Yvj9NF8rcvblUdfO"}
{"name":"Tough","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Dwarves are durable folk , hewn from the underpinnings of the Earth. Dwarves round up when factoring their Mortal Wound.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KUIWCvz2hUZ7t9UA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Z6Qlf25dkrl3eQdq"}
{"name":"Stout","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Dwarves are smaller than Men in stature, but they tend to be a bit thicker around the middle, with attendant broader hands, feet and arms. Though tough and doughty, Dwarves' stout frame also hinders them slightly. Speed must always be lower than their Power or Forte (whichever is higher), even if this limits advancement. Their stride is 6.\n\nDwarven nature allows for a Forte maximum of 9 rather than 8 and a Speed maximum of 6 rather than 8.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KUIWCvz2hUZ7t9UA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"eFZ1AnOI8wA4PdPa"}
{"name":"Greed","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"Deep in the heart of every Dwarf lies a terrible seed, a lust for wealth and beauty. Some Dwarves master it; others succumb. It is a powerful emotion that drives many a Dwarf from his comfortable life and compels him to perform terrible acts or zealously create works of inestimable craft. See the Dwarven Greed section in this chapter for more on this emotional attribute.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven common trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"All auditory-based Perception tests","obModifier":1,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Bastard","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven common trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fBxryWHsqibnhLIC"}
{"name":"Slave to Fate","type":"trait","img":"icons/commodities/tech/cog-gold.webp","data":{"pointCost":null,"name":"","traittype":"character","text":"The Rune Caster is plagued with fleeting visions of what could be and what might have been. He sees his own fate intertwined with all the other doomed strands; there is no other path to walk but the one he is on.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarven lifepath trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":0,"dieModifierTarget":"","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"","reputationDice":0,"reputationInfamous":false,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarven lifepath trait"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TtqjBPpwU1Bk1I1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gEu5hjMRH6m4bxT3"}
{"name":"Avarice","type":"trait","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","data":{"pointCost":3,"name":"","traittype":"die","text":"A player may choose to make his Dwarven character especially Greedy. With this trait, he can raise his character's starting Greed to whatever exponent he desires (so long as it is higher than what it would start at). The downside of this is that Greed tests always count as the type of test the character needs to advance, no matter the obstacle. If he needs a routine, the next test counts as routine. See the Greed mechanics for the ramifications of this.\n\nRestrictions: Dwarves only, special trait","collapsed":true,"hasAptitudeModifier":false,"aptitudeModifier":0,"aptitudeTarget":"","hasDieModifier":false,"dieModifier":1,"dieModifierTarget":"Animal Husbandry, Riding","hasObModifier":false,"obModifierTarget":"","obModifier":0,"addsReputation":false,"reputationName":"Apostate","reputationDice":1,"reputationInfamous":true,"addsAffiliation":false,"affiliationName":"","affiliationDice":0,"callonTarget":"","restrictions":"Dwarves Only"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"TmE39BSdpoka2VQY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MTlAT5d3M20TLtKg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_dgubyrm4iyo","path":"TRAITS#/CF_SEP/Dwarven Traits","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"iO5rrs5ei1RzanGI"}
